<div id="review_2037735308" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2037735308" />
    <a title="Olivier Delaye" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9854601-olivier-delaye"><img alt="Olivier Delaye" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1582470792p2/9854601.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2037735308?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Olivier Delaye" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Olivier Delaye" href="/user/show/9854601-olivier-delaye">Olivier Delaye</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2037735308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3004909429056219047">Some books come into your life exactly at the right time for you to welcome them with open arms. This is one of them. I wanted fast-paced action, and I got it. I wanted half-real/half-madeup pseudo-science kind of a la Crichton, and I got it. I wanted scary, and I got that by the bucketload. I wanted at least one great character to get to know and care about and have fun hanging out with, and I got him—I mean, Pendergast is amazing and his personality is so endearing I’d have a hard time finding</span>
  <span id="freeText3004909429056219047" style="display:none">Some books come into your life exactly at the right time for you to welcome them with open arms. This is one of them. I wanted fast-paced action, and I got it. I wanted half-real/half-madeup pseudo-science kind of a la Crichton, and I got it. I wanted scary, and I got that by the bucketload. I wanted at least one great character to get to know and care about and have fun hanging out with, and I got him—I mean, Pendergast is amazing and his personality is so endearing I’d have a hard time finding reasons not to adore him. So yeah all in all I took my sweet time getting into this series, considering it came out for the first time in 1995, but I’m oh so glad I did and will for sure read the sequels. Five stars all the way!</span>
  <a data-text-id="3004909429056219047" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
