<div id="review_2296268851" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2296268851" />
    <a title="kartik narayanan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4070035-kartik-narayanan"><img alt="kartik narayanan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1521695201p2/4070035.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2296268851?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="kartik narayanan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="kartik narayanan" href="/user/show/4070035-kartik-narayanan">kartik narayanan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2296268851" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11313057345080864659">Whew! I just finished Relic and it was mind blowing. The pacing and atmosphere make this an intense read like nothing else. The story is simple &amp; straightforward - in the words of Hudson (Aliens), its a bug hunt. But what a bug hunt. I am still getting over it.<br/><br/>I have seen the movie before and it is quite forgettable. The book is way better - in terms of characterization, the dialogues as well as the sense of creeping dread one gets as the book progresses.<br/><br/>In conclusion, it is a great read. Go for</span>
  <span id="freeText11313057345080864659" style="display:none">Whew! I just finished Relic and it was mind blowing. The pacing and atmosphere make this an intense read like nothing else. The story is simple &amp; straightforward - in the words of Hudson (Aliens), its a bug hunt. But what a bug hunt. I am still getting over it.<br /><br />I have seen the movie before and it is quite forgettable. The book is way better - in terms of characterization, the dialogues as well as the sense of creeping dread one gets as the book progresses.<br /><br />In conclusion, it is a great read. Go for it. <br /><br /><a href="https://digitalamrit.com" rel="nofollow noopener">My blog</a> has more reviews like this one.</span>
