<div id="review_3247161824" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3247161824" />
    <a title="Antoinette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette"><img alt="Antoinette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1503842818p2/5328952.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3247161824?book_show_action=true">Mar 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antoinette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antoinette" href="/user/show/5328952-antoinette">Antoinette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3247161824" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3279101957652228575">3.5 STARS<br/>This was a pulse pounding suspense thriller. Having started this series at Book #3, I decided to go back to the beginning. I did enjoy this book, but not as much as the third and fourth book. Found this one to be too gory and more thriller than mystery. In fact, I think if I had started the series with this one, I would not have continued.<br/>My favourite FBI agent, Pendergast, was not the focus in this one. He shared time with Margo Green, a museum employee , Lieutenant d’Acosta, of the Ne</span>
  <span id="freeText3279101957652228575" style="display:none">3.5 STARS<br />This was a pulse pounding suspense thriller. Having started this series at Book #3, I decided to go back to the beginning. I did enjoy this book, but not as much as the third and fourth book. Found this one to be too gory and more thriller than mystery. In fact, I think if I had started the series with this one, I would not have continued.<br />My favourite FBI agent, Pendergast, was not the focus in this one. He shared time with Margo Green, a museum employee , Lieutenant d’Acosta, of the New York PD, a reporter and a few other characters. I prefer when more time is spent with Pendergast and his intricate brain.<br />As I was reading it, I kept thinking of the movie “Poseidon Adventure”- everyone trapped somewhere in this museum and trying to escape. Who will make it, who won’t? Of course, the movie took place on a ship, but it had that same feel to it.<br /><br />Good escapist fiction! </span>
  <a data-text-id="3279101957652228575" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


